UID:10008905-1774170000-1774173600@catonsvillepres.org
SUMMARY:Adult Education
DESCRIPTION:Join us as we journey together through Lent with a six-part discussion of Rowan Williams’ beautiful book Being Disciples: Essentials of the Christian Life. William is the former Archbishop of Canterbury and one of the leading theologians of our time. Jesus called disciples to follow him\, to walk with him into the kingdom\, the realm of God’s justice and wholeness. What does it mean for us to be disciples? This is one of the most important questions we need to ask ourselves these days. “Discipleship\,” says Williams\, “is a state of being. Discipleship is about how we live; not just the decisions we make\, not just the things we believe\, but a state of being.” Books will be available for purchase on Sunday\, February 22. Cost: $10.
URL:https://catonsvillepres.org/event/adult-education-7/2026-03-22/
LOCATION:Library
CATEGORIES:Adult Education
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://catonsvillepres.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Bearwalk_CPC_10.18__253.jpg
END:VEVENT
